Interactive elements are the one of the most powerful features of Pvideo. They extend the familiar video format by giving the viewer control over the information which is displayed. This article takes a closer look at how interactive elements can be added to a scene or pop-up and configured.

## Add call to action (CTA) elements
To add a CTA element to the selected scene or pop-up:

- Open the **scene editor**.

- In the **sidebar**, go to **Interactions**.

- Click **Add**.

A CTA element will be added to the timeline.

### Configure CTA elements
Click on the CTA element in the playback area or its timeline layer to open the settings:

- **Event**

**Label:** Enter the internal label of this CTA element. It will be displayed on the Storyboard

- **Event type:** Select the type of action that should be performed when the CTA button is clicked

Event type

Destination

Configuration options

**Open link**

Enter a **Link URL**

Select where the link **Destination** should be opened:

**New window**

- **Same window**

**Open video**

Enter a **Link URL**

Select the **Video type**:

- **MP4**

- **Babelee video**

**Mail to**

Enter an **Email address**

**Call to**

Enter a **Phone number**

**Open pop-up**

Connect this CTA button [to a pop-up](/doxee-platform/docs/pvideo-designer-create-a-video-flow#integrate-a-popup) in the Storyboard editor

**Go to scene**

Connect this CTA button [to a scene](/doxee-platform/docs/pvideo-designer-create-a-video-flow#connect-two-scenes) in the Storyboard editor

- **Duration:** Enter the exact timestamps to control the start and end of the element

- **Appearance:** Enter a text to be displayed in the button, adjust the text formatting and visual formatting of the button

- **Size and position:** Set the size and position of the text element and lock the aspect ratio

> Tip

The size and position of the element can also be adjusted in the playback area using intuitive drag-and-drop controls.

- **Delete:** Delete this element and its timeline layer
